---
description: RAG pipeline rules: chunking, embeddings, retrieval, generation, ingestion.
globs: backend/app/rag/**,backend/app/workers/**
alwaysApply: false
---

# Chunking
- Structure-aware, clause-level chunking as an isolated, unit-tested module.
- Preserve section number, heading, page, and cross-references as metadata. No naive
  fixed-size chunking.

# Embeddings
- One embedding function and version for BOTH documents and queries. Store the model name and
  version with each vector. Never mix embedding models across documents and queries.

# Retrieval
- Hybrid: dense (pgvector) plus sparse (BM25 via pg_search, or tsvector), fused with
  Reciprocal Rank Fusion, then reranked. Always tenant-scoped.

# Generation
- Send only reranked, tenant-scoped clauses to Claude via Bedrock with a strict grounding
  system prompt.
- Every claim cites a clause. If no retrieved clause supports the answer, respond that it was
  not found in the user's documents. Never fabricate a citation.
- Return structured citations (document id, chunk id, section) so the viewer can highlight them.

# Ingestion
- Idempotent, keyed by document id, retryable. Failures go to the dead-letter queue and set
  status to failed with a reason. Status flow: processing -> ready -> failed.
